This is the Perl distribution Web-Scraper-Filter-Pipe.

INSTALLATION

Web-Scraper-Filter-Pipe installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is
set up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan Web::Scraper::Filter::Pipe

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Web-Scraper-Filter-Pipe documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Web::Scraper::Filter::Pipe

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

Marcel Gruenauer
